    public class ChessPieceMap
extends java.util.HashMap<ChessPoint,ChessPiece>
    The ChessPieceMap class for the chess project. This class extends a superclass of Hashmap. This is used as the basis for a chess board.

      • put

        public ChessPiece put(ChessPoint point,
                      ChessPiece piece)
               throws ChessException
        The put method for the ChessPieceMap class. It adds a ChessPoint/ChessPiece entry to the map. Null values are not permitted. This method is identical to put, but throws an exception if the given point is not a valid square on a chess board, or the given value is null.
        Specified by:
        put in interface java.util.Map<ChessPoint,ChessPiece>
        Overrides:
        put in class java.util.HashMap<ChessPoint,ChessPiece>
        Parameters:
        point - The key for the new entry.
        piece - The value for the new entry.
        Returns:
        The value previously associated with the key, or null if none.
        Throws:
        ChessException - Throws ChessException if the given key is not a valid square on a chess board, or if the given value is null.
